text:
Harry S. Truman (president)
Harry S. Truman was a President of the United States.
Biography
In 1948, President Truman visited Owl Cave in Twin Peaks, Washington.
Harry S. Truman of Twin Peaks, born in 1950, was named after President Truman by his father. There was no familial relation between them.
By 1952, Truman was a high-ranking Mason and allegedly ordered Nathan F. Twining to help organize a secret UFO task force designated Majestic 12.
